Key Match Events: Keshav Maharaj hit the winning runs for South Africa.
Tabraiz Shamsi took four wickets, restricting Pakistan's scoring rate.
Aiden Markram scored an excellent knock but fell nine runs short of his century.
Shaheen Shah Afridi dismissed Quinton de Kock and David Miller.
Usama Mir, a concussion substitute, dismissed Aiden Markram and Rassie van der Dussen.
Haris Rauf's stunning caught and bowled removed Lungi Ngidi.
Haris Rauf almost won it for Pakistan by trapping Tabraiz Shamsi lbw, but the decision was umpire’s call.
Pre-Game Insights: Babar Azam emphasized Pakistan’s focus on improving their powerplay performance.
South Africa's regular skipper Temba Bavuma returned to lead the side.
Kagiso Rabada was not part of the playing XI due to a lower back spasm.
Miscellaneous Highlights: South Africa bowled in sizzling temperatures without Kagiso Rabada.
Pakistan maintained an attacking approach for much of their innings.
Tabraiz Shamsi's return to the side was impactful with key middle-order wickets.
South Africa's big-hitting top order got off to a flier in their chase.
Marco Jansen played a crucial cameo for South Africa.
Shaheen Shah Afridi and Haris Rauf bowled brilliantly in the final overs.
